<TITLE> BFF to start U-15 camp in Khulna within a week </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 15 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh Football Federation intends to start the Under-15 booters' training camp for the AFC U-16 Championship in the next seven to 10 days in Khulna. Bangladesh have been drawn in Group E along with Japan, Taipei, Mongolia, the Philippines and Indonesia and the top two teams will advance into the 16-team finals. BFF general secretary Al Mussabir Sadi said that they had already picked a 40-member squad from 45 footballers, who were picked from the talent hunt programme across the country earlier this year, for a period up to the start of Ramadan. Bangladesh have appealed for hosting the Group E matches, which are scheduled to be held from October 3 to 18. Meanwhile, national coach Edson Silva Dido will return back to BKSP on Thursday to supervise the eight-week training camp of the national team as the national coach came back to the capital on Tuesday after seeing no electricity supply at the players' dormitory during the load shedding. Though it will take the BKSP authority a week to provide a generator, the BFF itself will arrange one from Thursday until then. Besides, the equipment Dido needs to conduct the training camp only reached the BKSP Tuesday arrived, but it was supposed to reach on Monday. The supplier took two days to deliver i
